<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Beautiful hotel; great for art lovers!! We had a wonderful stay at the Hotel Cortes. It is a beautiful colonial building with a great courtyard. The rooms were clean and as a former hermitage, appropriately furnished in a simple fashion. No frills, but definetly comfortable. The staff was excptionally friendly and informative. Its not in the safest neighborhood, (like most of mexico city) but the staff was very helpful in arranging reliable roundtrip transportation from the front door of the hotel. The Hotel Cortes is in a great location, walking distance (15 min) to the Zocalo, Cathedral, and the main temple ruins, 3 blocks from the Bellas Artes and is across the street from the Alameda and 1 block from the museum which houses one of Diego Riveras greatest Murals (Dream of A Sunday Afternoon in the Alameda). Numerous other museums and points of interest near by. The Metro station is on the corner and will take you anywhere you need to go.It is a bit loud from the restaurant setup in the courtyard, but there is so much to see that you will appreciate the wakeup call. Not to mention, the food served is pretty good, and pretty busy during lunch and dinner from locals. 
