<Author>evening
<Content>Deserves a better rating! What a nice little hotel! I've wanted to stay here since it was featured on The Amazing Race 3, so booked a night prior to a weekend trip to Taxco. Wanting to try different hotels, I booked the cushier Sheraton Centro Historico for my return after Taxco.Met the owner Santiago Brockmann, who was extremely knowledgeable about art and travel and made several excellent museum recommendations. The computers were down when I checked in - luckily - because the standard room I had paid for was not yet cleaned, so they put me in another room they knew was definitely available - one of the newly renovated executive suites. The suites are twice the size of the regular rooms and on the ground floor. If you're noise sensitive or want to sleep late, this isnt the best option because they start to set up breakfast at about 630am and you hear it all... But, if you need something to force you out of bed to go sightseeing, this is perfect. All the rooms face the beautiful courtyard - and it was actually cool in the morning (compared to the AC equipped Sheraton Centro). Good TV options - CNN, BBC and a German news channel in English. They had only the good FOX, not news.When I decided there was too much to see in Mexico City and cancelled Taxco, I debated moving to the cushier Sheraton right away, but the Cortes was so nice, I stayed another night. I got a $77 business travelers rate by comparing prices on this site. 
