<Content>Very nice hotel in the centre of Mexico City Lovely historic hotel within walking distance of the Zocalo and historic city centre sights. The Turibus (open top bus which takes you on a circular tour of the city) stops within 100 yards of the hotel entrance, very useful for visiting the anthropological museum without relying on taxis.The rooms are situated around a courtyard restaurant which serves food from breakfast to about 11 at night. Lots of businesss type people eat here during the day - so don't expect any afternoon naps!The food in the restaurant is good and reasonably priced.The rooms are quite small and overlook the courtyard, we stayed in both ground floor and first floor rooms, I would recommend staying on the first floor as the ground floor rooms can be a bit claustrophobic. 
